405-01-012	API - Input Processing	
User input must be validated, filtered, and sanitized to only allow valid data value, parameters, data types, and data patterns. This helps to protect against common vulnerabilities such as XSS, SQL Injection, Command injection, etc.
The Host header in the request must be validated to ensure that it matches the hostname of the API being called.
