405-01-015	API - Logging & Monitoring Requirements	
Enable logging at both the API gateway and service level to log user behaviors to support the detection of suspicious behavior. (e.g. failed login attempts, denied access, token reuse, unauthorized access attempts, endpoint enumeration, input validation errors, crashes, core dumps, unsecured deserialization, etc.).
Sensitive data such as access tokens, secret tokens, client secrets, PII, etc., must not be stored in logs.
Further security logging requirements are detailed in the Information Security Technology Usage Guidelines (800-05-001).

