405-01-050	API - Gateway Requirements	
Bank APIs published for reuse must be front ended by a bank approved API gateway.
Excludes APIs used only by components within a single contained system or service mesh.
All inbound API traffic from the internet or B2B partners must route through a bank approved API gateway.
Outbound API traffic from an internal bank source to an external destination may use an API gateway as a proxy, but it is not required.
Review API Gateway Best Practices and API Gateway Decision Matrix for more information.
For all other scenarios refer to API Gateway Best Practices and API Gateway Decision Matrix.
